        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:34PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Badin Lake, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
High Point, Asheboro, Randleman, North Carolina Zoo, Thomasville,
Seagrove, Trinity, Liberty, Ramseur, and Denton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
